    </div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>The most obvious sign is a loud bang—it sounds like a gunshot or firecracker. You might also notice your garage door won't open more than a few inches, the door feels extremely heavy when you try to lift it manually, or the opener motor runs but the door doesn't move. If you see a gap in the spring coil (it looks like it's split in two), your spring is definitely broken. Our free <a href="/homeowner-tools/door-diagnosis" style="color: #c57b30;">DoorDiagnosis™ tool</a> can help you confirm the issue in under 60 seconds.</p>
